(8, 610, 'Bahl Paper Mills Pvt. Ltd Aliganj Road, Kashipur , US Nagar', '78.9340367', '29.157867', 'Mr Raj Bhandari , GM ', 'Dr  Shivaker  Mishra ( CPPRI) , Dr Nitin Endlay ( CPPRI ) &  Dr Ankur Kansal ( UEPPCB)  ', '78307010009', 'bahlpapermills@gmail.com', '152421636531313.pdf', '', '', '152421636529366.pdf', '2018-04-05', '1.	Based on the analysis ,  the mill is achieving environmental compliance with respect to stipulated norms\r\n\r\n2.	A variation has been observed in the results  of analysis  of the treated effluent sample collectd and OCEMS reading recorded at the time of sample collection,. The  mill may be advised to calibrate the OCEMS  periodically. \r\n', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(9, 609, 'Prolific Papers Pvt Ltd, Aliganj Road, Kashipur , US Nagar', '78.9340367', '29.157867', 'Mr Zulfiqar Ali , GM\r\n\r\n', 'Dr S.Mishra & Dr.Nitin Endlay (CPPRI)Dr. Ankur Kansal & Mr.Yogesh Singh Rawat (UEPPCB', 'M 9997480786', 'zulfiqar@prolificpapers.com', '152421692112202.pdf', '', '', '152421692118331.pdf', '2018-04-05', 'As per the test report  ( of PCRI , an EPA recognized lab )  the mill is achieving compliance  with  respect  stipulated environmental norms \r\nThe results of the test report  and the OCEMS  reading  at the time of sample collection are in close proximity \r\n', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(10, 432, 'Diesel Locomotive Works,Manduadih, Varanasi', '82.9739 E', '25.3176 N', 'Shri. P.J. Chako, Shri Rahul Srivastava', 'Prof. S.N. Upadhyay, Prof. P.K. Mishra, Ms. Deepika Kushwaha (Ph.D.), Mr. Gopal Srivastava (TS), Mr. Kuldeep(TS)', '9794862206, 9794861201', 'dycedlw@gmail.com', '152422181727935.pdf', '15242218176252.pdf', '', '152422181732309.doc', '2018-04-02', 'Unit should obtain consent for handling hazardous waste (oil and sludge). \r\nSolid waste is being dumped just outside the ETP boundary. The organization should make arrangement for creating a landfill for this purpose.\r\nProper arrangement should be made for disposing of the detritus matter and grit from ETP.\r\nQuantification and characterization of dried sludge cake should be carried out\r\n', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(11, 875, 'APOLO DYEING HOUSE, JANGI ROAD, MIRZAPUR', '82.550815', '25.130739', 'Shri Rajeev Rai', 'Prof. S.N. Upadhyay, Prof. P.K. Mishra, Ms. Deepika Kushwaha (Ph.D.), Ms. Ishita Mishra (Scientist), Mr. Kuldeep (TS)', '9838722195', 'appolodyeingcenter@gmail.com', '152422253625826.jpg', '1524222536115.pdf', '152422253627440.pdf', '152422253629609.docx', '2018-04-07', 'The unit should try to harness solar energy and do water harvesting.\r\n\r\nWaste wool fiber should be properly collected and disposed of or can be used as soil nutrient after decomposition.', 'Temporary Closed', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(12, 650, 'HINDUSTAN UNILEVER LTD. 63 GARDEN REACH ROAD . KOLKATA 700024', '88.2953503', '22.5457061', 'MR. RUDRA PRATAP', '1. Prof. Dr. Asis Mazumdar, Director,SWRE ,JU2.Prof. Dr. Arunabha Majumder, Emeritus Professor,SWRE,JU3. Dr. Panka Kumar Roy,Associate Professor,SWRE,JU4.Dr.Gourab Banerjee,SRF,SWRE,JU5.Mr. Bimalendu Mal, AEE,WBPCB', '9167112427', 'rudra.pratap@unilever.com', '', '', '', '152455888114088.pdf', '2018-04-13', 'Compiled.  Details recommendation has been made in the attached inspection report.', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(13, 917, 'SWASTIK DYEING HOUSE (M/s Yash Creation), NATAVA,MIRZAPUR', '82.564434', '25.133699', 'Shri Bajarang Mundhra', 'Prof. S.N. Upadhyay, Prof. P.K. Mishra, Ms. Deepika Kushwaha (Ph.D), Ms. Ishita Mishra (Scientist), Mr. Kuldeep (TS)', '9336404330', 'yash_creation@india.com', '152456277431343.pdf', '15245627749084.pdf', '', '15245627745125.docx', '2018-04-07', 'Operators suppose to be running the ETP should be given proper training\r\n\r\nThe unit has enough land area to use the treated effluent within its premises, install rain water harvesting facility and solar panel for electricity generation.\r\n\r\nThough the operational area within the plant was relatively cleaner but there is scope to improve further', 'Non_Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(14, 630, 'RBNS Suagr Ltd, Laksar', '78.12722222', '29.93694444', 'Shri S.P. Singh, Sr. DGM (Production)', 'Arjesh Sharma, Sr. DGM (PCRI), Narendra Agarwal, Sr. Manager (PCRI), Pradeep Kumar, Sr. Lab. Asstt. (PCRI)', '9837791037', 'edprbns@yahoo.com', '152462971430567.pdf', '152462971426900.pdf', '', '15246297141469.pdf', '2018-04-05', 'MGF has been installed. \r\nFlow meter at DM Plant, Condensate, ETP inlet, Vacuum Filter and Pan Station has been installed.\r\nExcess condensate from Sugar mill is being taken in the distillery unit CPU.\r\nAnalysis of drain water passing near Sugar Unit is being done on regular basis. \r\nPhotographs are also attached in Consent Copy Folder.', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
(15, 623, 'RBNS  Sugar (Distillary Unit), Laksar', '78.03166667', '29.74638889', 'Shri S.P. Singh, Sr. DGM ', 'Arjesh Sharma, Sr. DGM (PCRI), Narendra Agarwal, Sr. Manager (PCRI), Pradeep Kumar, Sr. Lab. Asstt. (PCRI)', '9837791037', 'edprbns@yahoo.com', '152463049410049.pdf', '', '', '152463049413542.pdf', '2018-04-06', '1. Photographs are attached in Inspection Report (Annexure 11, 12, 13)\r\n2. It has been observed that the plant is not having any rain water harvesting facility. It is suggested to install Rain Water Harvesting System.\r\n3. It is observed that covered area in Bio-compost yard for the storage and finished product is smaller than the CPCB guidelines. Hence, necessary arrangements should be made to meet the compliance of CPCB guidelines.\r\n4. It is observed that municipal drain is passing through the factory premises. Hence, it is suggested that regular analysis of water quality should be carried out to ensure any short circuiting of waste water streams from distillery.', 'Complied', '', '', '', '', 0, '', 0),
